35:08.938 --> 35:11.708
Anyhow, if the same habitual
response were to be combined

35:11.741 --> 35:14.244
with say strumming
or beating a bongo,

35:14.277 --> 35:17.313
I just think that you would have
an easier time with your patients.

35:17.346 --> 35:20.650
And that's exactly why your
time isn't wasted here, Raina.

35:20.683 --> 35:23.286
I know,
you are right, of course.

35:23.319 --> 35:24.955
It's just that Neurocon
is in a few weeks,

35:24.987 --> 35:26.790
and even if I used
your facility,

35:26.822 --> 35:29.659
I mean where am I going to get
the patients to study?

35:29.692 --> 35:32.996
Hmm. Good point.
Thank you.

35:33.663 --> 35:36.933
Raina, let me show you
something, very quickly here.

35:39.002 --> 35:40.337
Hmm?

35:40.904 --> 35:44.041
Ah, this is Den.
He is from India.

35:44.074 --> 35:47.578
- He was a patient of mine a long, long time ago.
- Wow.

35:47.610 --> 35:51.648
Look, he is dancing.
He is loving this music. He is so happy.

35:51.681 --> 35:56.587
You know there are tons of advocates
for alternate therapies outside the U.S.

35:56.619 --> 36:00.657
In fact, I know someone,
Dr. Sen.

36:00.690 --> 36:05.995
She and I were college roommates and now she is
the director of the Hope Institute in Kolkata.

36:06.029 --> 36:09.800
- Kolkata.
- Kolkata. - Mm-hmm.

36:09.833 --> 36:13.470
As prophetic as that sounds,
there's no time for me to go to India.

36:13.502 --> 36:17.073
Raina, you can always
reschedule your review cycle.

36:17.107 --> 36:19.643
Research worth
doing is worth doing right.

36:20.377 --> 36:23.413
Okay, India.
Max would freak.

36:23.447 --> 36:24.348
Yeah.

36:30.619 --> 36:31.955
Max, dinner's here.

36:31.987 --> 36:34.324
Were you going to get it?
Well, I suppose I'm buying, too.

36:34.357 --> 36:35.926
Money is on the table.

36:43.400 --> 36:44.835
Really? Indian food?

36:46.737 --> 36:47.738
We need to talk.

36:50.473 --> 36:51.542
I'm getting pizza.

37:08.558 --> 37:11.895
I signed...

37:11.927 --> 37:17.699
signed up for music therapy.

37:17.701 --> 37:23.741
- And you should come, too.
- Hmm.

37:23.773 --> 37:25.109
Please.

37:25.141 --> 37:30.413
Very funny, what next you want
me to sign up for <i>American Idol?</i>

37:30.447 --> 37:36.020
<i>American Idol,</i> very funny.

37:36.953 --> 37:42.726
Doctor is coming from...

37:44.860 --> 37:47.130
America,

37:47.163 --> 37:51.567
for special research.

37:56.873 --> 38:00.476
Here's the address.
The Hope Institute.

38:00.509 --> 38:05.515
- First time here, Madam?
- Yes. It's beautiful.

38:05.549 --> 38:07.717
That was just the airport.

38:08.717 --> 38:13.790
Victoria Memorial, Park Street,
<i>Maidan,</i>

38:19.628 --> 38:21.464
Beautiful colors.

38:21.498 --> 38:23.801
If you are tired of buildings,
Madam,

38:23.833 --> 38:28.906
nightclubs, shopping,
new market, AC Market.

38:29.605 --> 38:31.007
Sounds good.

38:58.802 --> 39:00.504
Thank you.

39:04.808 --> 39:07.878
- Good luck, Madam.
- Thanks.

39:09.980 --> 39:14.083
- Dr. Sen, Raina Wilson.
- Huh, please come.

39:15.051 --> 39:17.487
- Glad to meet you.
- You, too.

39:17.520 --> 39:19.856
- Well, I will show you around.
- Yeah.

39:22.292 --> 39:25.728
It's so wonderful to see a facility
of this size focused on disabilities.

39:25.761 --> 39:30.533
We consider the Hope Institute a
place of possibility not disability.

39:30.567 --> 39:32.770
That's my challenge also.

39:35.672 --> 39:38.175
- I'll show your apartment, come.
- Okay. - Come.

39:40.911 --> 39:43.581
Hopefully you'll find
it before too long.

39:46.049 --> 39:49.920
Well, we have several
students signed up for you.

39:50.853 --> 39:53.823
- Thanks.
- Get some rest, I will see you later.

39:53.857 --> 39:55.092
Okay. Thanks.

40:10.639 --> 40:14.911
Tanya, severe cerebral palsy.
Adite, Down syndrome.

40:14.944 --> 40:20.551
Niladri, acute leukemia, severe
migraines, paralysis of the spine.

40:21.150 --> 40:25.721
Jeeja, Misty, Palek, Brent,
Miguel, Tanya, Adite, Niladri.

40:25.755 --> 40:28.225
Jeeja, Misty, Palek, Brent.

40:31.795 --> 40:35.197
- Good morning, everyone.
- Good Morning.

40:35.230 --> 40:38.301
- My name is Raina.
- Hi. - Hi.

40:38.902 --> 40:41.338
I am your new
teacher from America.

40:41.371 --> 40:43.206
Can everyone say the name Raina?

40:43.239 --> 40:45.074
Raina.

40:45.107 --> 40:47.343
Very good, what is your name?

40:47.377 --> 40:49.980
- Shruti.
- Shruti, that's a beautiful name.

40:50.614 --> 40:52.148
- What is your name?
- Jeeja.

40:52.181 --> 40:54.250
Jeeja. Lovely name.

40:56.085 --> 40:59.089
- Now you guys are all lucky, you know why?
- Why?

40:59.121 --> 41:04.728
Because, all of you only have
to learn one name, Raina,

41:04.761 --> 41:08.264
but I have to learn all of your
names to get to know you, right?

41:08.297 --> 41:10.333
Well, how am I going to do that?

41:11.134 --> 41:14.304
Well, they say you can learn
a lot about someone

41:14.337 --> 41:16.974
by what kind of music they like.

41:17.007 --> 41:20.844
So, I'm going to play some
songs, some different songs,

41:20.877 --> 41:23.147
and see
what you guys respond to.

41:25.681 --> 41:29.285
- Come in.
- She can't hear you.

41:36.692 --> 41:37.860
Come.

41:55.944 --> 41:58.881
- No fighting, no fighting, are you okay?
- Hmm.

41:58.915 --> 42:00.683
- Okay?
- Hmm.

42:00.717 --> 42:02.185
You want to sit down?

42:05.922 --> 42:08.759
Thank you.
You are my new best friend.

42:09.259 --> 42:11.661
Come, come to the class.

42:12.429 --> 42:14.197
Yes, join, join.

42:14.230 --> 42:18.701
It was horrible and all I kept thinking was Max
told me not to use nursery rhymes as music.

42:18.735 --> 42:22.006
Yeah, sounds like you could have
destroyed some eardrums, Raina.

42:23.373 --> 42:25.376
Why don't you come back before
someone actually gets hurt?

42:26.042 --> 42:29.279
Huh, it took me a day to get here.
I couldn't even turnaround if I wanted to.

42:31.047 --> 42:32.215
Well, make it quick.

42:33.215 --> 42:35.685
I had to wash my gig clothes
and I ruined my favorite vest.

42:36.152 --> 42:38.355
Babe, I told you that
needed to be dry-cleaned.

42:38.388 --> 42:42.292
Well, I didn't know that.
I don't do my own laundry, Raina.

42:42.324 --> 42:44.360
So you owe me big.

42:45.261 --> 42:46.697
I do?

42:48.165 --> 42:50.967
Listen, Max, I gotta get to sleep
okay, so I... I'll call you soon?

42:52.802 --> 42:54.071
No, Raina.

42:54.404 --> 42:58.007
Hello?
Unbelievable.

43:11.286 --> 43:13.022
- Hey, Claud.
- <i>Hi, Raina.</i>

43:13.056 --> 43:18.195
Listen, so I just wanted to let
you know, day one, disastrous.

43:18.228 --> 43:20.831
Hang on. I'm just going to
get some tea, one sec.

43:22.799 --> 43:26.103
<i>Wow!</i>

43:26.136 --> 43:28.237
Yeah, may be give
me someone else to talk to.

43:28.270 --> 43:29.973
<i>Hey, don't
forget to look up Den.</i>

43:30.005 --> 43:31.273
<i>I'm sure he'd love to help.</i>

43:31.306 --> 43:34.110
Oh, Claud, I'm so sorry.
I totally forgot.

43:34.143 --> 43:36.078
- I'll look up Den tomorrow, okay?
- <i>Okay.</i>

43:36.112 --> 43:37.748
Bye, Claud.

43:42.786 --> 43:44.088
This is Den.

43:45.455 --> 43:48.991
Den, she is Raina Wilson
from America.

43:49.025 --> 43:53.230
She is researching on
music therapy at Hope Institute.

43:53.263 --> 43:56.098
Nice to meet you.
I'm a colleague of Dr. Claudia.

43:56.132 --> 43:57.868
Oh.

43:57.900 --> 44:00.103
- Den is an avid music fan.
- Yes.

44:00.136 --> 44:02.239
So I've heard.
Maybe you can help me out.

44:02.272 --> 44:03.206
Sure.

44:06.009 --> 44:09.846
<i>In his hospitality,
Den showed me that in India,</i>

44:09.878 --> 44:13.350
<i>there is a musicality
and rhythm, in everyday life.</i>

44:16.985 --> 44:18.821
This is my therapy.

44:18.855 --> 44:23.025
Nature has music
for those that listen.

44:23.826 --> 44:26.962
- I think you are the second best friend I've made in India.
- Okay.

44:26.996 --> 44:30.868
The first better be amazing or I'll be offended.

45:08.871 --> 45:09.973
My first best friend.

45:10.005 --> 45:12.174
Yeah, I'm not offended.

45:14.344 --> 45:16.279
Okay, now that everyone's here,

45:16.311 --> 45:21.150
my friend Den here believes that
you can find music in nature.

45:21.183 --> 45:24.388
So let's see what kind of
sounds nature can make, okay?

45:31.094 --> 45:32.362
Yay!

45:32.395 --> 45:35.931
Let's hear the sound
of the rain. Ready?

45:42.505 --> 45:45.475
Now, lighter rain.

46:40.964 --> 46:44.534
Stop, stop, stop. Okay. No.

46:47.270 --> 46:48.672
Oh, no!

46:52.208 --> 46:54.244
Guys, guys, guys.

46:55.078 --> 47:00.016
Sit down. Sit down. Come on, come on.
Sit down. Sit down.

47:00.049 --> 47:03.052
Sit, sit, sit.
Relax, relax.

47:03.085 --> 47:06.022
- Come, come.
- Oh, God!

47:06.054 --> 47:10.159
- You need more best friends now?
- Yeah, I think so.

47:10.192 --> 47:12.027
<i>Raina, listen to me.</i>

47:12.060 --> 47:14.296
<i>I insist that you come home
as scheduled.</i>

47:14.330 --> 47:16.333
<i>This is my life uprooted, too.</i>

47:18.000 --> 47:20.203
Oh, yes.

47:20.235 --> 47:22.605
What? What?
Is someone there with you?

47:23.306 --> 47:26.042
What? No.

47:26.074 --> 47:27.377
You know you're the one who told
me that if...

47:27.409 --> 47:30.346
I would fail without any
concrete research, right?

47:31.080 --> 47:34.049
You think I'm here having an affair
with an Indian guy in a wheelchair?

47:34.083 --> 47:37.721
<i>I don't know Raina,
put me on a video chat.</i>

47:38.688 --> 47:41.992
Look, I'm going to calling you
when I know my schedule, okay?

47:42.025 --> 47:43.193
Love you.

47:50.366 --> 47:54.471
<i>♪ Twinkle, twinkle Little star ♪</i>

47:54.503 --> 47:59.241
<i>♪ How I wonder what you are ♪</i>

47:59.275 --> 48:03.713
<i>♪ Up above the world so high ♪</i>

48:03.746 --> 48:07.517
<i>♪ Like a diamond in the sky ♪</i>

48:25.368 --> 48:29.072
<i>The happy boy Niladri
made friends easily.</i>

48:29.105 --> 48:30.340
<i>He loved to write poems.</i>

48:31.440 --> 48:33.743
I couldn't speak always,
you know.

48:33.775 --> 48:35.344
When I was a kid,

48:35.811 --> 48:40.150
my parents sent me to a doctor,

48:40.850 --> 48:44.121
friend of Raina's in America.

48:45.621 --> 48:49.325
Priya was the first girl
in my life

48:49.357 --> 48:53.462
who never thought
I am different.

48:59.201 --> 49:03.305
Being with you
has changed my life.

49:03.706 --> 49:06.476
Thanks for being my girlfriend.

49:08.610 --> 49:12.815
We? We could never be
boyfriend and girlfriend. Huh.

49:31.833 --> 49:36.739
Den, Den. What happened?
Den, Den, Den.

49:52.788 --> 49:56.359
Hi.
Oh, that sounds wonderful.

49:57.426 --> 49:59.761
I thought I was
in a festival for a minute.

50:04.433 --> 50:06.436
Why not have them put on a show?

50:07.235 --> 50:09.873
Mm-hmm, give them a goal.

50:09.906 --> 50:12.775
Uh, I've already bit off
more than I can chew.

50:13.409 --> 50:16.579
Um, I can help.

50:16.612 --> 50:18.181
- Yeah?
- Mm-hmm.

50:19.214 --> 50:20.549
Hmm, okay.

50:20.583 --> 50:23.453
I have another staff member
helping me organize a small concert

50:23.485 --> 50:25.420
to keep the students
interested in music,

50:25.453 --> 50:28.690
I just can't pinpoint that
measurable goal to reach.

50:28.723 --> 50:30.559
Hey, how's Den?

50:31.493 --> 50:32.594
He's good.

50:32.628 --> 50:36.665
I mean there was some drama,
but he's been a big help.

50:37.299 --> 50:43.205
Remember, it's not always the physicality
of the condition that's most debilitating.

50:43.239 --> 50:46.909
It's the mental condition
that is wrongly imposed.

50:46.942 --> 50:50.946
"It's the mental condition
that is wrongly imposed", right?

50:50.980 --> 50:53.349
Have you done
any sightseeing or anything?

50:53.382 --> 50:56.186
No. I can't... I don't...
I don't have time.

50:56.219 --> 50:58.421
Don't tell me
you don't have the time.

50:58.453 --> 51:01.891
You'll never gauge your progress if you
don't get out for a fresh perspective.

51:02.558 --> 51:05.494
<i>As your mentor, I insist.</i>

51:05.527 --> 51:08.497
- Okay. Okay. Bye.
- <i>Bye.</i>

51:10.632 --> 51:12.435
- <i>"Thoughts...</i>
- Jeeja.

51:12.467 --> 51:14.803
<i>...the childhood days
of sheer bliss..."</i>

51:18.440 --> 51:19.743
What's wrong?

51:20.442 --> 51:23.446
- Niladri.
- Sorry.

51:26.815 --> 51:30.619
You know when I first met him,
he told me he felt very lucky

51:30.652 --> 51:32.621
because besides his mother,

51:32.654 --> 51:35.557
his two best friends were the
most beautiful girls in the world.

51:35.590 --> 51:37.092
- Mm-hmm.
- Yeah.

51:37.125 --> 51:40.362
- <i>Will I be able to pursue my dreams, my studies?</i>
- Yeah.

51:40.395 --> 51:43.565
<i>The significant
others both young and old,</i>

51:43.598 --> 51:49.471
<i>they cheer me up and cheering,
"Yes, you can. Of course, you can."</i>

51:49.505 --> 51:51.208
He is right about his luck.

51:51.873 --> 51:54.877
You two are his angels on Earth.
You know that.

51:55.578 --> 51:57.679
And now
he gets to be your angel.

51:57.712 --> 51:59.381
That's what friends are for,
right?

51:59.781 --> 52:01.083
Good way to think of it.

52:01.116 --> 52:04.319
<i>As I look into the
vastness of the evening sky</i>

52:04.353 --> 52:06.856
<i>and watch the birds
returning to their nests,</i>

52:06.889 --> 52:10.693
<i>I am once more lost
in the realm of my thoughts.</i>

52:10.726 --> 52:12.028
You know what?

52:12.060 --> 52:13.362
We could really use a diversion,

52:13.395 --> 52:16.531
so how about
you be my travel partners?

52:16.565 --> 52:19.569
<i>Niladri will always be
remembered for his creations.</i>

52:19.601 --> 52:22.638
<i>His disability was brought on
by acute Leukemia.</i>

52:24.806 --> 52:26.575
Surprise.

52:28.476 --> 52:33.750
<i>And for those who cannot articulate
their emotional or physical pain, as a society,</i>

52:33.782 --> 52:36.819
<i>we need to bring other forms of
communication into their lives.</i>

52:36.851 --> 52:38.620
Open. Turn it on. Right.

52:38.654 --> 52:44.027
<i>Oddly enough, text messaging is a big step
towards realizing that we are all connected.</i>

52:45.895 --> 52:49.632
<i>This realization offered me
the opportunity to help Angel</i>

52:49.665 --> 52:52.835
<i>who by being hearing impaired
was my greatest challenge.</i>

52:58.741 --> 53:03.380
- Thank you.
- Welcome, my pleasure, my pleasure.

53:04.880 --> 53:08.685
Okay. Go slow. Go slow.

53:08.717 --> 53:09.752
Oh, oh.

53:11.619 --> 53:13.389
- Wait, wait.
- Okay.

53:28.503 --> 53:31.473
Surely, we will stop by
the temple on our way back.

53:31.507 --> 53:33.376
Absolutely.

53:38.413 --> 53:40.449
It could be hard going home,
you know.

53:40.482 --> 53:42.618
Especially after
you've been gone a long while.

53:42.650 --> 53:44.321
I feel like it's been months
since I left America.

53:45.154 --> 53:47.489
Why did you come
all the way to India?

53:47.522 --> 53:50.459
Simple. I needed
a supportive environment

53:50.493 --> 53:52.895
to, uh, research what I believe
is an important tool

53:52.927 --> 53:54.897
to the functioning
of the human brain.

53:56.031 --> 54:00.636
Raina, wouldn't it be easier

54:00.668 --> 54:05.007
to research normal brains?

54:05.040 --> 54:07.110
Why not research normal brains?

54:07.743 --> 54:10.612
Well, that's the whole point,
what makes a brain normal, right?

54:10.645 --> 54:13.014
What you feel
or what's popular opinion?

54:13.047 --> 54:16.518
People here are more receptive to
not worrying about popular opinion.

54:17.520 --> 54:19.722
Ego's everywhere, huh.

54:19.755 --> 54:24.060
The way I see it when people
think that you're a freak

54:24.092 --> 54:26.596
and you've got nothing to lose,

54:26.628 --> 54:29.031
you can't fall off the floor,
right?

54:29.063 --> 54:32.835
You can't fall off the floor?
Okay. Right.

54:39.074 --> 54:44.813
Raina, what made you
want to be a brain doctor?

54:44.846 --> 54:47.516
- What made me want to be a brain doctor?
- Yeah.

54:47.549 --> 54:49.584
Hmm. Curiosity.

54:49.618 --> 54:51.788
When I found out that this...
this little spongy thing up there

54:51.821 --> 54:54.556
that weighs less than a pound
was responsible for everything,

54:54.589 --> 54:56.758
I guess
I just wanted to know how.

55:07.569 --> 55:13.875
Aren't you curious
about other body parts,

55:13.909 --> 55:17.079
- like the heart?
- The heart? - Yes.

55:17.112 --> 55:18.714
Sure I'm interested
in the heart,

55:18.746 --> 55:21.183
just not in a scientific way.

55:44.706 --> 55:46.942
Oh, my Anil.

55:51.547 --> 55:54.016
Oh, Angel.

56:47.036 --> 56:49.972
- Come, come. You must be Den.
- Yeah.

56:50.005 --> 56:51.807
This is my friend Raina
and Jeeja.

56:51.839 --> 56:53.976
- Nice to meet you.
- <i>Namaskar.</i>

56:54.643 --> 56:55.811
- Thanks.
- Come, come, come.

57:05.688 --> 57:08.958
- These rains can seep to your bones.
- Thank you.

57:12.627 --> 57:13.929
Thank you.

57:15.197 --> 57:16.766
Please, have it.

57:18.032 --> 57:20.904
I have a question.

57:28.143 --> 57:29.279
My son.

57:31.112 --> 57:33.015
They were very close.

57:36.150 --> 57:39.054
I am lucky to have him
as long as I did.

57:40.288 --> 57:42.891
Angel just didn't understand
death.

57:44.025 --> 57:48.096
After that I enrolled her in the
local school for special needs.

57:48.130 --> 57:49.298
Mm-hmm.

57:49.331 --> 57:52.001
- Where she met Dr. Sen.
- Oh.

57:58.940 --> 58:00.676
Thank you.

58:03.811 --> 58:06.114
You are looking beautiful.

58:10.185 --> 58:11.788
Hello.

58:12.388 --> 58:14.757
I heard an Angel is here.

58:24.799 --> 58:25.801
Hmm.

58:29.003 --> 58:32.141
This is good.
I can't. That's it.

58:32.174 --> 58:34.342
Thank you for your hospitality.

58:34.375 --> 58:37.379
I wish we had a doctor
like you sooner.

58:37.413 --> 58:38.581
Oh, thank you.

58:38.614 --> 58:41.984
Who are we to say what the
right time is, she is here now.

58:42.016 --> 58:44.686
Oh, so sweet.

58:45.286 --> 58:49.091
If you don't mind me asking,
how did Angel's mother die?

58:56.364 --> 58:59.132
Complications during childbirth.

59:02.837 --> 59:08.310
Our people thought that
when someone was born,

59:08.342 --> 59:11.946
- not right, they were cursed.
- Hmm.

59:11.980 --> 59:14.717
That's why we named her Angel.

59:14.750 --> 59:15.685
Hmm.

59:15.717 --> 59:19.355
But, uh, her mother
could not take the guilt

59:19.388 --> 59:24.226
and she felt responsible,
so she ended her life.

59:25.893 --> 59:31.066
Thankfully we had
another angel here to help.

59:42.210 --> 59:46.348
Oh, my goodness.
Beautiful tea garden.

59:46.380 --> 59:47.917
Yeah, wow.

59:59.895 --> 01:00:02.230
Mrs. Borah, come here and dance.

01:00:02.264 --> 01:00:07.370
<i>Music unites people of different backgrounds
no matter what the socioeconomic setting is.</i>

01:00:44.172 --> 01:00:47.042
- Just don't bother.
- There's got to be a ramp.

01:00:48.043 --> 01:00:51.547
I doubt wheelchairs were invented
during the time this was built.

01:00:54.148 --> 01:00:56.551
Please move on,
I will join you later.

01:00:56.585 --> 01:00:58.521
