01:10:09.370 --> 01:10:11.873
Go on.

01:10:14.476 --> 01:10:17.946
And now the soothing
sounds of classical music.

01:10:24.052 --> 01:10:27.723
No sleeping. I see you.
Don't fall sleep. Okay.

01:10:37.065 --> 01:10:40.902
Next, we are going to listen to
someone that I know very well.

01:10:40.935 --> 01:10:43.772
My boyfriend from America
has a heavy metal band,

01:10:43.804 --> 01:10:45.740
so let's see
if you guys like this.

01:10:56.817 --> 01:10:58.887
Okay, okay.

01:11:02.856 --> 01:11:05.092
Everybody relax.

01:11:07.195 --> 01:11:12.467
Out, it's out. It's out. Okay.
Relax. Everybody relax.

01:11:22.643 --> 01:11:24.879
<i>The longer I stayed in India,</i>

01:11:24.913 --> 01:11:29.118
<i>the more I realized what a perfect
place it was to study music therapy.</i>

01:11:30.084 --> 01:11:32.821
Come,
I will take you to that side.

01:11:35.923 --> 01:11:37.792
You know,

01:11:37.825 --> 01:11:42.530
- raga is not meant to be composed.
- Mm-hmm.

01:11:42.563 --> 01:11:46.601
It's...
it's sort of a generator,

01:11:47.168 --> 01:11:49.204
like the Deepak Raga

01:11:49.236 --> 01:11:53.708
when sung properly
can create fire,

01:11:54.709 --> 01:11:56.545
but that doesn't matter,

01:11:56.578 --> 01:11:58.446
there is the Megh Mallar

01:11:58.480 --> 01:12:02.651
which brings the rain
down to sooth the Earth.

01:12:09.057 --> 01:12:12.527
<i>Their culture is known
for keeping the body in harmony,</i>

01:12:12.560 --> 01:12:17.865
<i>and this mindfulness is made possible
through rhythm, vibration, and music.</i>

01:12:17.898 --> 01:12:19.234
Let's go that side.

01:12:19.267 --> 01:12:22.070
Is that the story
you wanted to tell me?

01:12:25.973 --> 01:12:31.480
I knew a teacher who had
a boy in her class,

01:12:32.112 --> 01:12:34.182
who did not like to study.

01:12:34.214 --> 01:12:39.520
- Never paid attention, never responded to her.
- Mm-hmm.

01:12:39.553 --> 01:12:44.926
But one day she was
humming a song and he liked it.

01:12:46.527 --> 01:12:50.965
- He asked her to sing along.
- Right.

01:12:50.999 --> 01:12:56.137
- So she said that, yes, I will sing if you study...
- Mm-hmm.

01:12:56.169 --> 01:12:58.873
...and he gladly did so
after that.

01:12:58.906 --> 01:13:00.875
What was the song?

01:13:00.909 --> 01:13:04.012
The song was based
on Raga Bhairav,

01:13:05.012 --> 01:13:07.114
it stimulates the heart

01:13:07.882 --> 01:13:13.120
and it made him feel
a sense of security,

01:13:13.954 --> 01:13:18.092
love, and fearlessness.

01:13:19.994 --> 01:13:22.864
It's... it's important
to all of us

01:13:22.896 --> 01:13:27.268
- and it makes us all feel the same way.
- Right.

01:13:27.302 --> 01:13:31.806
But it is more important
for an autistic child.

01:13:31.838 --> 01:13:33.774
Hmm. I believe you.

01:13:35.910 --> 01:13:39.548
You know, the whole universe

01:13:39.981 --> 01:13:44.652
- is created by energy.
- Mm-hmm.

01:13:44.686 --> 01:13:48.723
- Including colors and sounds.
- Mm-hmm.

01:13:50.892 --> 01:13:53.295
It all connects us together,

01:13:53.328 --> 01:13:59.868
each one of us
to the sound of <i>Omkara.</i>

01:14:01.201 --> 01:14:02.102
<i>Omkara.</i>

01:14:14.115 --> 01:14:17.352
Excuse me, can you tell me where
